    "problemStatement": "Given three integer arrays, the task is to find three integers, one from each array such that they sum up to a given target value X. Print the output depending on whether such triplet exits or not.\n\nExamples:\n\n    Input: arr1[]={2} , arr2[]={11,6,7} ,arr3[]={4,5},X=12\n\n    Output:Yes\n\n    arr1[0]+arr2[1]+arr[3]=2+6+4=12",
    "constraints": [
      "1 <= N,X <= 10^9"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "The first line has the size of each arrays.\n\nNext lines have the elements of the arrays.\n\nAnd the last line has the X values",
    "outputFormat": "Print the first triplet if found else print \"No such triplets\"\n\nNote:\n\n    Print the first occurance the triplets.",
